abstract: Scientists estimate that there are 37.2 trillion cells in average human body, and between 100 billion and 200 billion galaxies in known universe, putting number of human cells far higher than number of galaxies.
lead_paragraph: The counting does not come easily, or exactly, but there are estimates for the number of cells in the human body and galaxies in the observable universe.
